title: Bleu De Channel
description: A clean, woody fragrance. Easily one of the best to go Colognes for everyday use. Depending on the season either get the EDP for colder weathers or the EDT for warmer weathers.

title: Acqua Di Gio by Armani
description: If you're looking for that fresh ocean-clean scent then this is for you! I bought this last year and haven't looked back

title: Dior Sauvage
description: Classic MUST HAVE!!!! This is the type of cologne that transcends time and fashion. If you want to stand out from the crowd.... this is the one!

title: Tobacco Oud Tom Ford
description:
My first impression… This is a scrubber. So I was going to give my bottle to a friend.
But, before I did… I gave it a second wearing. Both my late-teens daughter and wife really liked it. So I kept it.

title: Versace Eros
description: If you're looking for an energizing scent to give you a pick-me-up through a long day at the office, this is definitely the one to choose.

title: Invictus Intense Paco Rabanne
description: Best perfume I've ever owned! It's the epitome of manliness and cleanliness. Begins with a powerful scent of pungent pepper then transitions into a sweet yet light citrusy composition with a perceptible background of whiskey.

title: Versace Dylan Blue
description: Literally just smells like a shower gel. I mean it’s good if you wanna smell “just out of the shower” but that’s really all it’s good for. Not really worth it!

title: La Nuit de l'Homme Yves Saint Laurent
